<!DOCTYPE html>
<!-- The Doctype defines the document type and the the html version -->
<html>
    <head>
        <title>The First Page</title>
        
    </head>
    <body>
        <h1>Using a h1 element</h1>
        <h2>Using a h2 element</h2>
        <h3>Using a h3 element</h3>
        <h4>Using a h4 element</h4>
		<h5>Using a h5 element</h5>
		<h6>Using a h6 element</h6>
        
		<!-- A dotted line in purple -->
		<div class="aligncenter" style="width:400px;height:0;border-top:2px dotted #880088;font-size:0;">-</div><br>
		
        <!-- These are comments in HTML -->
        <div>
			<!-- The br element does not need a space or slash in ordinary html but does so in xhtml -->
            Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit.<br />
            <!-- The i element will transform text into italics -->
            <i>Proin eget augue id massa auctor accumsan.</i><br />
			<hr />

            <!-- The b element will transform text into bold -->
            <b>vulputate justo et volutpat dictum.</b> <br />
        </div>
        
        <!-- Paragraph element -->
		<!-- The strike element strikes through the phrase that it surrounds  -->
		<!-- They are known as inline or nested commands -->
        <p>
            <strong>Phasellus in augue velit. <strike>Cras pellentesque enim nibh</strike>, et cursus nunc tincidunt eu. </strong><br />
            <small>Pellentesque sapien tellus, vestibulum vel risus quis, dapibus luctus massa.</small><br />
            
		</p>
		<br>
		
		<!-- Centres the text in the page but may not be available in some versions -->
		<center>
			<p>
				Pellentesque nec quam mauris. Sed sed ultricies nisl.<br>
			</p>
		</center>
		
		<hr />
		<p>
            Suspendisse a ex eu lorem interdum pulvinar. Morbi suscipit libero mi, vel pharetra felis imperdiet sit amet. <br />
            Mauris posuere, erat non laoreet auctor, sapien lectus aliquet orci, vitae tempus quam metus ac turpis.<br />
        </p>
		
		<!-- Pre tag defines preformatted text -->
		<!-- Browsers normally render pre text in a fixed-pitched font, with whitespace intact, and without word wrap. -->
		<pre>
			Text in a pre element
			is displayed in a fixed-width
			font, and it preserves
			both      spaces and
			line breaks
		</pre>
		
		<!-- 
			NBSP elements insert  non breaking space which is different than normal space
			as it stops a phrase being broken into a new line
		-->
		<p>
			Class&nbsp;aptent&nbsp;taciti sociosqu ad litora torquent per conubia nostra, per inceptos himenaeos
		</p>
		
		<!-- The hr element inserts a horizontal rule line -->
		<hr />		
		
		<p>
			Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Cras auctor tempor nisl, at ullamcorper nulla suscipit venenatis. 
			Sed eu efficitur leo. Aenean sit amet ultrices lectus. Ut velit odio, bibendum nec lectus sit amet, porta euismod libero. 
			Nunc vitae ligula hendrerit, rhoncus ex vulputate, efficitur nibh. Ut ullamcorper convallis erat ut maximus. 
		</p>
		
		<p>
			Nunc tincidunt risus non lacus eleifend, eu egestas diam lacinia. Sed quam nibh, eleifend eu elit vel, hendrerit feugiat arcu. 
			Cras ut augue finibus metus condimentum porta. Mauris congue pretium scelerisque. Duis maximus vestibulum diam id lacinia. 
			Maecenas feugiat vestibulum mauris, at porttitor ante varius vitae. Quisque placerat, urna nec aliquam vehicula, metus erat semper sem, at blandit velit odio vitae nunc.
		</p>
		
		<!-- The &copy may not work in some browsers -->
